isoiec80000:term-t13-24-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "information content"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t13-24-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "I(x)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t13-24 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "13-24" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t13-24-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t13-24-0 ;
  skos:definition """stem:[I(x)] +
stem:[= lb 1/p(x) \" Sh\"] +
stem:[= lg 1/p(x) \" Hart\"] +
stem:[= ln 1/p(x) \" nat\"]

where stem:[p(x)] is the probability of event stem:[x]
"""@en ;
  skos:note """One shannon is the quantity value when the argument
is equal to two.

stem:[1 \" Sh\" ~~ 0,693 \"unitsml(nat)\" ~~ 0,301 \" Hart\"]

One hartley is the quantity value when the argument
is equal to ten.

stem:[1 \" Hart\" ~~ 3,322 \" Sh\" ~~ 2,303 \"unitsml(nat)\"]

One natural unit of information is the quantity value
when the argument is equal to stem:[e], Euler's number.

stem:[1 \"unitsml(nat)\" ~~ 1,433 \" Sh\" ~~ 0,434 \" Hart\"]

See <<iec60050-171,droploc%locality:item=\"171-07-14\">>.
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-Sh ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-Hart ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-nat ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-13 .